            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Is this correct? `int`, `long` and `bool` are not interpreted as C types but rather as Python types. For C types one must use `cython.int`, etc.",
            "commit_id": "cfe15e1c5402abe72dee1bf0fb272ab995d3fb53",
            "created_at": "2026-01-31T21:29:42Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -232,6 +232,10 @@ Further pointer types can be constructed with ``cython.pointer[cython.int]``\n and arrays as ``cython.int[10]``. A limited attempt is made to emulate these\n more complex types, but only so much can be done from the Python language.\n \n+Pure python mode also supports type qualifiers ``const`` and ``volatile``,\n+which can be applied using ``cython.const[cython.int]`` and\n+``cython.volatile[cython.int]``. For more details see :ref:`type_qualifiers` section.\n+\n The Python types int, long and bool are interpreted as C ``int``, ``long``",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7491#discussion_r2750045145",
            "id": 2750045145,
            "line": null,
            "node_id": "PRRC_kwDOABDGAc6j6lvZ",
